  "prompt": "What is the most depressing song?",
  "response": "The most depressing song can vary greatly depending on personal experiences and associations, but some songs are commonly regarded as particularly somber or melancholic. For instance, \"Hurt\" by Nine Inch Nails (and its cover by Johnny Cash), \"Tears in Heaven\" by Eric Clapton, and \"Creep\" by Radiohead are often noted for their deep emotional themes and haunting melodies. Additionally, \"The Night We Met\" by Lord Huron and \"Nothing Compares 2 U\" by Sin\u00e9ad O'Connor also resonate with feelings of loss and heartache. Ultimately, the \"most depressing\" song is subjective and can differ from person to person.",
